{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.21",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 21 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:1",
      "text": "But Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:2",
      "text": "Hear diligently my speech, and let this be your consolations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:3",
      "text": "Suffer me that I may speak; and after that I have spoken, mock on.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:4",
      "text": "As for me, is my complaint to man? and if it were so, why should not my spirit be troubled?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:5",
      "text": "Mark me, and be astonished, and lay your hand upon your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:6",
      "text": "Even when I remember I am afraid, and trembling taketh hold on my flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:7",
      "text": "Wherefore do the wicked live, become old, yea, are mighty in power?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:8",
      "text": "Their seed is established in their sight with them, and their offspring before their eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:9",
      "text": "Their houses are safe from fear, neither is the rod of God upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:10",
      "text": "Their bull gendereth, and faileth not; their cow calveth, and casteth not her calf.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:11",
      "text": "They send forth their little ones like a flock, and their children dance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:12",
      "text": "They take the timbrel and harp, and rejoice at the sound of the organ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:13",
      "text": "They spend their days in wealth, and in a moment go down to the grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:14",
      "text": "Therefore they say unto God, Depart from us; for we desire not the knowledge of thy ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:15",
      "text": "What is the Almighty, that we should serve him? and what profit should we have, if we pray unto him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:16",
      "text": "Lo, their good is not in their hand: the counsel of the wicked is far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:17",
      "text": "How oft is the candle of the wicked put out! and how oft cometh their destruction upon them! God distributeth sorrows in his anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:18",
      "text": "They are as stubble before the wind, and as chaff that the storm carrieth away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:19",
      "text": "God layeth up his iniquity for his children: he rewardeth him, and he shall know it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:20",
      "text": "His eyes shall see his destruction, and he shall drink of the wrath of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:21",
      "text": "For what pleasure hath he in his house after him, when the number of his months is cut off in the midst?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:22",
      "text": "Shall any teach God knowledge? seeing he judgeth those that are high.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:23",
      "text": "One dieth in his full strength, being wholly at ease and quiet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:24",
      "text": "His breasts are full of milk, and his bones are moistened with marrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:25",
      "text": "And another dieth in the bitterness of his soul, and never eateth with pleasure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:26",
      "text": "They shall lie down alike in the dust, and the worms shall cover them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:27",
      "text": "Behold, I know your thoughts, and the devices which ye wrongfully imagine against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:28",
      "text": "For ye say, Where is the house of the prince? and where are the dwelling places of the wicked?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:29",
      "text": "Have ye not asked them that go by the way? and do ye not know their tokens,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:30",
      "text": "That the wicked is reserved to the day of destruction? they shall be brought forth to the day of wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:31",
      "text": "Who shall declare his way to his face? and who shall repay him what he hath done?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:32",
      "text": "Yet shall he be brought to the grave, and shall remain in the tomb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:33",
      "text": "The clods of the valley shall be sweet unto him, and every man shall draw after him, as there are innumerable before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.21.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:34",
      "text": "How then comfort ye me in vain, seeing in your answers there remaineth falsehood?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
